Description: Plastic box (with yeallow label '13') with transparent lid containing numerous fragments of papyrus.
Curator's comments: Previously unregistered material stored in Papyrus Store. Label reads '2 layers Papyrus fragments - various texts + vignettes. 2 marked polythene bags containing fragments.' A note by Stephen Quirke reads 'New Kingdom BD fragments, with orange-yellow border in 1 case; Third Int Period (?) vign with two columns hieratic left, funerary; Late Period hieratic fragment; Greek fragment; Coptic fragment. Stored Students Room JAN 1992'. The fragments inside are unmounted and unglazed.
